        <div class="body">
            <p>The "ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE" is proprietary syntax introduced in MySQL 4.1.  It is not standard SQL, and other RDBMS brands do not support it.</p>

<p>The workaround is to attempt the insert(), catch the exception if there is a duplicate key violation, and then perform the update() instead.  This works on all RDBMS brands.</p>

